To create a DbContext class for the healthcare management system, first, install Entity Framework Core in your project. You can do this using the Package Manager Console or NuGet. Here's the command for the Package Manager Console:

```
Install-Package Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.SqlServer
```

After installing the required package, here's a sample DbContext class for the models provided:

```csharp
using Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore;
using System;

namespace HealthcareManagementSystem.Models
{
    public class HealthcareDbContext : DbContext
    {
        public HealthcareDbContext(DbContextOptions<HealthcareDbContext> options) : base(options)
        {
        }

        public DbSet<Patient> Patients { get; set; }
        public DbSet<HealthcareProvider> HealthcareProviders { get; set; }
        public DbSet<Appointment> Appointments { get; set; }
        public DbSet<Medication> Medications { get; set; }
        public DbSet<Facility> Facilities { get; set; }

        protected override void OnModelCreating(ModelBuilder modelBuilder)
        {
            base.OnModelCreating(modelBuilder);

            modelBuilder.Entity<Patient>().ToTable("Patient");
            modelBuilder.Entity<HealthcareProvider>().ToTable("HealthcareProvider");
            modelBuilder.Entity<Appointment>().ToTable("Appointment");
            modelBuilder.Entity<Medication>().ToTable("Medication");
            modelBuilder.Entity<Facility>().ToTable("Facility");
        }
    }
}
```

In this sample code, a new class called HealthcareDbContext is created, which inherits from the DbContext class provided by Entity Framework. The HealthcareDbContext class contains DbSet properties for each of the models you want to store in the database (Patient, HealthcareProvider, Appointment, Medication, and Facility).

The OnModelCreating method is overridden to define the table names for each of the models and set up any additional configurations that might be needed. In this example, we just set the table names for each model in the database to match the model class names.

