To make the `Appointments` field not required when creating a new patient, you can simply remove the appointments field from the form. When creating a new patient, the appointments list will be left empty and later updated when creating a new appointment for the patient.

First, make sure your `Patient` model in your `Models` folder doesn't have any data annotation attributes for the `Appointments` field, such as the `[Required]` attribute:

```csharp
public class Patient
{
    public int Id { get; set; }

    // Other fields...

    public ICollection<Appointment> Appointments { get; set; }
}
```

Next, ensure that the `Appointments` field isn't included in your patient `Create` view in the `Patients/Views/Create.cshtml` file (which it shouldn't be, as it does not make sense to include it in the add patient form).

By removing any `[Required]` data annotation attributes from the `Appointments` field and not including it in the add patient form, you ensure that the field is not required when creating a new patient. The appointments list will remain empty for the patient until new appointments are assigned to the patient.

