When an `Appointment` instance is queried from the database using Entity Framework Core, it will automatically track the `Appointment` and the associated `Patient` object, if it was eagerly loaded or lazy-loaded. Therefore, when you submit a form to create or update an `Appointment`, and you pass the retrieved `Appointment` object to the controller action, ModelState might automatically validate both the `Appointment` and its associated, tracked `Patient`.

